I have tested the output on a sequence labeling project. After I changed the format.ts the jsonl text label output isn't anymore the same as the jsonl output. 
I got the following outputs on example data:

Jsonl with text label:
`{"id": 4, "text": "example", "meta": {"wikiPageID": 1}, "annotation_approver": null, "comment_count": 0, "labels": [[0, 1, "LOC"], [0, 2, "ORG"]]}
{"id": 5, "text": "example", "meta": {"wikiPageID": 2}, "annotation_approver": null, "comment_count": 0, "labels": [[0, 1, "LOC"]]}
{"id": 6, "text": "example", "meta": {"wikiPageID": 3}, "annotation_approver": null, "comment_count": 0, "labels": [[0, 1, "PER"]]}`

Jsonl without text label:
`{"id": 4, "text": "example", "annotations": [{"label": 3, "start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 1, "user": 1, "created_at": "2021-04-03T19:54:42.369772Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-03T19:54:42.369797Z"}, {"label": 4, "start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 2, "user": 1, "created_at": "2021-04-03T19:54:42.374564Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-03T19:54:42.374586Z"}], "meta": {"wikiPageID": 1}, "annotation_approver": null, "comment_count": 0}
{"id": 5, "text": "example", "annotations": [{"label": 3, "start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 1, "user": 1, "created_at": "2021-04-03T19:54:42.376095Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-03T19:54:42.376114Z"}], "meta": {"wikiPageID": 2}, "annotation_approver": null, "comment_count": 0}
{"id": 6, "text": "example", "annotations": [{"label": 5, "start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 1, "user": 1, "created_at": "2021-04-03T19:54:42.377344Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-03T19:54:42.377363Z"}], "meta": {"wikiPageID": 3}, "annotation_approver": null, "comment_count": 0}`

Is the output format above the one you look for? What type of project do you use?
